H, TH, TTH, TTTH, ...
P(H)=\frac 12
P(TH)=\frac 14
P(TTH)=\frac 18
X
P(X=k) = \frac{1}{2^k}
P = 1 - P(X > k) = 1 - P(k \text{ tails}) = 1 - \frac{1}{2^k} = \frac{2^k - 1}{2^k}
P = \sum_{k=0}^\infty P(X=2k+1) = \sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac{1}{2^{2k+1}} = \frac{1}{2} \sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac{1}{4^k} = \frac{1}{2} \frac{1}{1- \frac{1}{4}} = \frac{2}{3}
P = \sum_{k=0}^\infty P(X=3(k+1)) = \ldots = \frac{1}{7}
P = P_b + P_c - \sum_{k=0}^\infty P(X = 3(2k+1)) = \ldots = \frac 2 3 + \frac 1 7 - \frac 1 8 \cdot \frac{1}{1 - \frac 1 {64}} = \frac{43}{63}
